name: At
description: @. Needed in CDCE prior to main DCE specification for syntactical purposes.

name: Begin separator
description: Begin a DCE separator string.

name: End separator
description: End a DCE separator string.

name: Range
description: The DCE range character. Used to represent ranges in DCE. See the wiki for more information.

name: Record summation
description: Used to denote the union of two records. See the wiki for more information.

name: Begin number
description: Begin a DCE number.

name: End number
description: End a DCE number.

name: Unknown value
description: Substitution character for an unknown value.

name: Gregorian calendar identifier
description: Internal DCE calendar identifier for the Gregorian calendar.

name: Positive
description: Positive value (syntactical representation — This is not the   character)

name: Negative
description: Negative (syntactical representation — This is not the − character)

name: Full drop back
description: Drop back to the core sheet (no meaning in EDF)

name: Drop back
description: Drop back to the enclosing sheet (no meaning in EDF)

name: Begin DCE content
description: Begins a DCE region (no meaning in EDF)

name: No mapping
description: Processing use only (not for interchange)

name: Space
description: Sometimes used as a word separator, e.g. in Anoé

name: Latin Capital Letter I
description: Special casing considerations for Turkish

name: Latin Small Letter I
description: Special casing considerations for Turkish

name: Begin unbounded content
description: This denotes content that is not "bound" (given a context of a page, etc.) to be within — in other words it is what a plain text file is to a word processing file with page formatting — content with no context given for presenting it

name: Vertical tabulation
description: Also used as a line separator by Microsoft Word and Powerpoint which use it to contrast with the character used as a paragraph separator (sources: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/3380538/what-is-a-vertical-tab http://unicode.org/reports/tr13/tr13-9.html )

name: New line
description: A variant of Dc120

name: Begin encapsulated UTF-8
description: Begin Base 64 encapsulated UTF-8

name: End encapsulated UTF-8
description: End Base 64 encapsulated UTF-8

name: Begin keyed embed fragment
description: This Dc is used for embedding arbitrary keyed ID/data pairs in a document. Standard structure: Followed by base64-encoded data identifying a fragment, then Dc 202 (End keyed embed ID sequence), then by the base64-encoded fragment itself, then by Dc 201 (End keyed embed fragment).

name: End keyed embed fragment
description: See description for 200

name: End keyed embed ID sequence
description: See description for 200

name: Begin encapsulated binary data
description: Arbitrary binary data (base64 encoded, no semantic significance assigned to it)

name: End encapsulated binary data
description: See description for 203

name: Unicode replacement character
description: Used to replace an incoming character whose value is unknown or unrepresentable in Unicode

name: Replacement character for unavailable Dc
description: Used to replace an incoming character whose value is not mapped to a Dc (document component)

name: Begin document
description: Beginning of a document
